de.fha.dpmi.modeling.bpmn.elements

Class ConnectingObjectSequenceFlowImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fha.dpmi.modeling.ModelRelationImpl
      • de.fha.dpmi.modeling.bpmn.elements.ConnectingObjectImpl
        • de.fha.dpmi.modeling.bpmn.elements.ConnectingObjectSequenceFlowImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConnectingObject, SequenceFlow, ModelRelation

    public class ConnectingObjectSequenceFlowImpl
extends ConnectingObjectImpl
implements SequenceFlow
    A sequence flow is a directed edge between two flow objects inside a pool. It defines the control flow between two nodes. A condition might be set which must be true in order to sequence the control flow.
